# Day 6 – AI Resume Optimizer

## What I Learned

Today I learned how AI can be used to analyze and improve a resume for ATS systems and recruiter readability.

## Original Resume Review

I uploaded my resume and asked Claude to evaluate it from an ATS and recruiter perspective.

### Key Observations

- Resume had a good technical foundation.
- Skills were present but could be organized better.
- Project descriptions needed stronger impact statements.
- Professional summary could be improved.
- ATS keyword coverage could be increased.

## Resume Optimization

Claude suggested several improvements:

- Stronger professional summary
- Better skill categorization
- Improved project descriptions
- More ATS-friendly structure
- Better readability for recruiters

## Before vs After

### Before

- Generic formatting
- Limited keyword optimization
- Basic project descriptions

### After

- Clear professional summary
- Improved ATS keyword coverage
- Stronger project presentation
- Better overall structure

## Key Learnings

- Resume structure matters.
- ATS systems rely heavily on relevant keywords.
- Project descriptions should highlight impact and outcomes.
- AI can identify weaknesses that are easy to miss manually.

## Conclusion

This exercise showed how AI can be used as a career tool. By analyzing and optimizing a resume, Claude helped make the document more ATS-friendly and recruiter-ready.
